-- Gol Linhas increases Boeing 737-800 aircraft orders
-- 
-- Thu Dec 27, 2007 6:32am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/27/us-gollinhas-fleet-idUSWNAS532720071227

 

 (Reuters) - Brazilian airline company Gol Linhas Aereas ( GOL.N ) ( GOLL4.SA ) said it exercised firm orders for 34 Boeing 737-800 aircraft, and signed a new contract to acquire 40 additional aircraft for delivery in 2012 to 2014. 

 Gol said the agreement increases the number of aircraft on order from 121 to 161, and is in line with its policy of reducing operating costs by running a standardized fleet. (Reporting by Shamik Paul in Bangalore; Editing by  Pratish Narayanan )